            <p>
                In this project, I handled the hands-on development side of the build. I took the lead on prototyping, testing, assembly, CAD modeling, repeated fitment checks, repeated system testing, and much of the research and design work that shaped the final version. That included working through how the door would physically package the electronics, how the locking hardware would fit, and how the system would behave once all of the components were integrated into one assembly.
            </p>
            <p>
                My teammates supported the project by helping with documentation and purchasing, which made it possible for me to stay focused on iteration and implementation. That workflow let us move faster while still keeping the project organized. It also reflected how engineering teams often work in practice: some members keep procurement and written deliverables moving forward, while others push the prototype itself through design changes, integration, and testing.
            </p>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Main areas I focused on</h3>
